{"record_type":"issue","dcat_version":"0.5.0","namespace":"tmp303guyqu","id":"4ose","title":"Platform Modernization Initiative","description":"Modernize the platform architecture and infrastructure to improve scalability, maintainability, and deployment efficiency. This is a critical multi-quarter initiative that will fundamentally change how our systems operate.\n\nKey objectives:\n- Migrate from monolith to microservices\n- Implement CI/CD pipelines\n- Improve observability and monitoring\n- Reduce deployment time from hours to minutes","status":"in_progress","priority":0,"issue_type":"epic","owner":"charlie@example.com","parent":null,"labels":["infrastructure","strategic","q1-2026","backend"],"external_ref":"PLAT-100","design":"## Architecture Overview\n\nThe platform will be decomposed into the following services:\n- **User Service** - Authentication, authorization, user management\n- **Order Service** - Order processing, fulfillment\n- **Inventory Service** - Stock management, reservations\n- **Notification Service** - Email, SMS, push notifications\n\nCommunication: gRPC for internal, REST for external APIs\nData: Each service owns its database (PostgreSQL)\nEvents: Kafka for async communication","acceptance":null,"notes":"Initiated after Q1 performance review. Expected to take 4-6 months with potential for phased rollout. Budget approved by leadership.","close_reason":null,"created_at":"2026-02-08T21:12:52.333747+01:00","created_by":"alice@example.com","updated_at":"2026-02-08T21:12:52.334071+01:00","updated_by":"bob@example.com","closed_at":null,"closed_by":null,"deleted_at":null,"deleted_by":null,"delete_reason":null,"original_type":null,"comments":[{"id":"tmp303guyqu-4ose-c1","issue_id":"tmp303guyqu-4ose","author":"alice@example.com","text":"Kickoff meeting scheduled for Monday. Please review the design doc beforehand.","created_at":"2026-02-08T21:12:52.333952+01:00"},{"id":"tmp303guyqu-4ose-c2","issue_id":"tmp303guyqu-4ose","author":"charlie@example.com","text":"Design doc looks solid. I have some questions about the Kafka setup - let's discuss in the meeting.","created_at":"2026-02-08T21:12:52.334019+01:00"},{"id":"tmp303guyqu-4ose-c3","issue_id":"tmp303guyqu-4ose","author":"bob@example.com","text":"Added this to the Q1 roadmap. Stakeholders are aligned on timeline.","created_at":"2026-02-08T21:12:52.334067+01:00"}],"duplicate_of":null,"metadata":{}}
{"record_type":"issue","dcat_version":"0.5.0","namespace":"tmp303guyqu","id":"4xlf","title":"Migrate to microservices architecture","description":"Break monolith into scalable microservices. This involves decomposing the application into domain-driven services that can be developed and deployed independently.\n\nPhase 1: Extract User Service\nPhase 2: Extract Order Service\nPhase 3: Extract remaining services","status":"in_progress","priority":1,"issue_type":"feature","owner":"charlie@example.com","parent":"tmp303guyqu-4ose","labels":["backend","architecture","microservices"],"external_ref":"PLAT-101","design":null,"acceptance":"- Service boundaries clearly documented\n- Service communication via well-defined APIs\n- Deployment pipeline supports independent service rollout\n- Documentation complete with architecture diagrams\n- Zero downtime during migration","notes":"Started with architectural assessment. Current focus: identifying service boundaries.","close_reason":null,"created_at":"2026-02-08T21:12:52.334146+01:00","created_by":"alice@example.com","updated_at":"2026-02-08T21:12:52.334189+01:00","updated_by":"charlie@example.com","closed_at":null,"closed_by":null,"deleted_at":null,"deleted_by":null,"delete_reason":null,"original_type":null,"comments":[],"duplicate_of":null,"metadata":{}}
