{"record_type":"issue","dcat_version":"0.5.0","namespace":"tmp303guyqu","id":"5wr9","title":"Should we use GraphQL or REST for the new API?","description":"Need to decide on API architecture for the new services. Both have tradeoffs.\n\n**GraphQL pros:** Flexible queries, single endpoint, strong typing\n**REST pros:** Simpler, better caching, more tooling support","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"question","owner":null,"parent":null,"labels":["architecture","api","decision"],"external_ref":"ARCH-701","design":null,"acceptance":null,"notes":"Need decision by end of sprint for planning purposes.","close_reason":"Decision: REST for public APIs, GraphQL for internal dashboard. Rationale documented in ADR-005.","created_at":"2026-02-08T21:12:52.338596+01:00","created_by":"charlie@example.com","updated_at":"2026-02-08T21:12:52.338802+01:00","updated_by":null,"closed_at":"2026-02-08T21:12:52.338632+01:00","closed_by":"alice@example.com","deleted_at":null,"deleted_by":null,"delete_reason":null,"original_type":null,"comments":[{"id":"tmp303guyqu-5wr9-c1","issue_id":"tmp303guyqu-5wr9","author":"diana@example.com","text":"GraphQL would be great for the dashboard - lots of flexible queries.","created_at":"2026-02-08T21:12:52.338712+01:00"},{"id":"tmp303guyqu-5wr9-c2","issue_id":"tmp303guyqu-5wr9","author":"frank@example.com","text":"REST is simpler for external consumers. Most of our customers expect REST.","created_at":"2026-02-08T21:12:52.338748+01:00"},{"id":"tmp303guyqu-5wr9-c3","issue_id":"tmp303guyqu-5wr9","author":"alice@example.com","text":"Let's do both - REST for public, GraphQL for internal. Best of both worlds.","created_at":"2026-02-08T21:12:52.338799+01:00"}],"duplicate_of":null,"metadata":{}}
